DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(79)90046-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199679900461
AB  - A model of the balance of payments is presented in this paper in which stock and flow effects are completely integrated. The model accounts for all flows of funds in the system and allows for the endogenous determination of the exchange rate. The model is first outlined in general terms and then a particular ‘quasi-empirical’ version of it is analyzed by means of simulation techniques. The results of analyzing this version show the likely importance of accounting for capital flows and price linkages among countries in the construction of multicountry econometric models.
