DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(79)90051-5
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199679900515
AB  - The sharp fluctuations in exchange rates in recent years have increased importers' and exporters' exchange rate risks considerably. There are various ways to cover these risks. This note provides a description of and empirical evidence on a number of these ways. The main conclusion is that during the 1970s Dutch traders covered by far the majority of their exports and imports in one way or another.
